  "prompt": "Why did the government of India introduced a 2000 rupee note instead of a new 1000 rupee note?",
  "response": "The Indian government introduced the \u20b92000 note instead of a new \u20b91000 note as part of its demonetization policy announced on November 8, 2016. The primary reasons for this decision were:\n\n1. **Disruption of Black Money and Counterfeit Currency**: The sudden demonetization of the existing \u20b9500 and \u20b91000 notes aimed to curb black money, corruption, and the circulation of counterfeit currency. By introducing a new \u20b92000 note, the government intended to make it harder for those hoarding black money to exchange their old notes without proper documentation.\n\n2. **Higher Denomination for Convenience**: The \u20b92000 note allowed for a higher denomination currency to be in circulation, which was necessary to meet the immediate cash demand of the economy. This helped in reducing the physical volume of currency needed and facilitated quicker replenishment of cash in the system.\n\n3. **Distinctive Design and Security Features**: The new \u20b92000 note was designed with advanced security features to make counterfeiting more difficult. Introducing a new denomination rather than just a new design of the \u20b91000 note added an extra layer of security and helped in distinguishing the new legal tender from the old, demonetized notes.\n\n4. **Psychological Impact**: The introduction of the \u20b92000 note, rather than a new \u20b91000 note, had a psychological impact on the public and those dealing in black money. It signaled a significant change and reinforced the government's commitment to tackling corruption and illegal cash hoarding.\n\n5. **Long-term Strategy**: The government also planned to increase the circulation of smaller denominations like the \u20b9500 and \u20b9200 notes to encourage a shift towards a less-cash economy. The \u20b92000 note was seen as a temporary measure to quickly address the cash crunch while these other denominations were ramped up.\n\nOverall, the introduction of the \u20b92000 note was a strategic move to address immediate economic needs while reinforcing the government's broader objectives of fighting black money and promoting digital transactions.",
